340 g Pork Chops, boneless
¾ cup Basmati Rice
2 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
1 tsp Garlic Salt
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
2 tbsp Sweet Chili Sauce
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water and half the garlic salt to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Once boiling, add rice, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, cut bok choy into 1-inch pieces. (TIP: Rinse bok choy leaves to wash away any hidden dirt!)
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch slices.
Add sweet chili sauce, whole grain mustard, half the soy sauce and 1/3 cup (1/2 cup) water to a small bowl. Stir to mix.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil then peppers and onions. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often until tender and lightly charred, 2-4 min.
Add bok choy and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Cook, stirring often until tender, 1-2 min. Remove from heat and stir in remaining soy sauce.
Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

Pat pork dry with paper towels.
Season with remaining garlic salt and pepper.
Heat the same pan over medium.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil then pork. Cover and cook until golden-brown, 2-3 min per side.

Add sauce mixture to pan and flip pork chops to coat and until sauce is warm and pork is cooked through, 1-2 min.**

Fluff rice with fork. Stir in veggies.
Thinly slice pork.
Divide rice between plates.
Top with pork.
Spoon sauce from pan over pork.